 advertising trade cards, stereoscopic photographs, picture postcards, magic lantern slide sets and films of early cinema. The book provides an in-depth study of this rich and fascinating corpus of popular visual media that has not been studied before, and the discourses that these images were meant to illustrate. This intermedial approach offers new insights into the emergence of national clichés and the study of stereotypical thinking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aClichés in motion pictures. 0aNational characteristics, Dutch. 0aStereotypes (Social psychology) in mass media. 0aStereotypes (Social psychology) in motion pictures. 0aStereotypes (Social psychology)zNetherlands. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press eBook Package 2018z978311060672040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048532971zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048532971zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048532971.jpg  a978-3-11-060672-0 Amsterdam University Press eBook Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-066731-8 AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA